@telic.definition: Entities that denote goals, purposes, or final objectives.

@agentive.definition: Entities that denote causes, origins, or motivations for events or actions.

@cause.definition: Entities or forces that produce effects or bring about changes.

@part.definition: Simple parts or fragments of entities.

@body_part.definition: Parts of the human or animal body.

@group.definition: Collections or sets of entities grouped together.

@human_group.definition: Groups or collectives composed specifically of humans.

@amount.definition: Quantities or degrees of measure for other entities.

@entity.definition: Stable things or beings in the world.

@locale.definition: General locations, either geographic or natural.

@geopolitical_location.definition: Political or administrative regions and locations.

@natural_feature.definition: Naturally occurring areas, surfaces or geographic forms.

@opening.definition: Holes, entries, or access points in physical space.

@building.definition: Constructed structures with an enclosed space.

@artifactual_area.definition: Man-made spaces used for activities or transit.

@material.definition: Substances used in the creation of other things.

@artifact.definition: Objects made or modified by humans for a purpose.

@artifactual_material.definition: Materials of artificial origin used to make artifacts.

@furniture.definition: Large movable equipment used to make a space functional.

@utensils.definition: Handheld tools used in domestic or practical tasks.

@toys.definition: Objects designed for play or entertainment.

@clothing.definition: Garments or attire worn on the body.

@container.definition: Objects used to hold or store other things.

@instrument.definition: Tools used to perform specific tasks or functions.

@money.definition: Items representing or storing financial value.

@vehicle.definition: Objects used to transport people or goods.

@semiotic_artifact.definition: Physical carriers of meaning or information.

@artifact_food.definition: Prepared or processed foods made by humans.

@ingredients.definition: Substances added to prepare or season food.

@physical_object.definition: Tangible, shaped, and naturally occurring entities.

@organic_object.definition: Physical entities with distinct boundaries and properties.

@animal.definition: Entities referring to animals or non-human living beings.

@human.definition: Entities referring to humans categorized by human.

@people.definition: Entities referring to humans categorized by people.

@people_by_age.definition: Entities referring to humans categorized by people by age.

@people_by_religion.definition: Entities referring to humans categorized by people by religion.

@people_by_morality.definition: Entities referring to humans categorized by people by morality.

@people_along_political_spectrum.definition: Entities referring to humans categorized by people along political spectrum.

@People_by_leisure_activity.definition: Entities referring to humans categorized by people by leisure activity.

@people_by_origin.definition: Entities referring to humans categorized by people by origin.

@people_by_ethnicity.definition: Entities referring to humans categorized by people by ethnicity.

@people_by_transitory_activity.definition: Entities referring to humans categorized by people by transitory activity.

@people_by_gender_or_sexual_orientation.definition: Entities referring to humans categorized by people by gender or sexual orientation.

@people_by_health_condition.definition: Entities referring to humans categorized by people by health condition.

@people_with_disabilities.definition: Entities referring to humans categorized by people with disabilities.

@people_by_persistent_activity.definition: Entities referring to humans categorized by people by persistent activity.

@people_by_profession.definition: Entities referring to humans categorized by people by profession.

@role.definition: Functions or identities assumed by individuals in a social or organizational context.

@people_by_ideo.definition: Entities referring to humans categorized by people by ideo.

@vegetal.definition: Entities referring to plants or vegetation.

@substance.definition: Materials or matter from which things are made.

@natural_substance.definition: Materials or matter from which things are made.

@substance_food.definition: Materials or matter from which things are made.

@drink.definition: Liquids that are consumed for refreshment or nutrition.

@artifactual_drink.definition: Objects or materials created or shaped by humans for a specific purpose.

@quality.definition: Abstract attributes or characteristics related to quality.

@dimension.definition: Attributes that quantify spatial, temporal, or other measurable aspects.

@sense.definition: Physiological faculties through which perception occurs.

@social_property.definition: Abstract attributes or characteristics related to social property.

@domain.definition: Fields of knowledge or areas of human activity.

@time.definition: Concepts referring to points or intervals on a temporal scale.

@moral_standards.definition: Norms or standards relating to right and wrong behavior.

@cognitive_fact.definition: Concepts related to knowledge, reasoning, or intellectual processes.

@movement_of_thought.definition: Collective ideologies or trends within society or thought.

@institution.definition: Organizations or structures with a social, legal, or cultural function.

@convention.definition: Socially or legally established rules or agreements.

@representation.definition: Entities that stand in for or depict something else.

@language.definition: Systems of communication using words or symbols.

@sign.definition: Elements used to convey meaning or represent concepts.

@information.definition: Content or data communicated or received through symbols or representations.

@number.definition: Numerical values expressing quantity or order.

@unit_of_measurement.definition: Standard quantities used to express dimensions or amounts.

@business.definition: Entities or concepts related to commerce, trade, or economic activity.
